/target

# Cargo.lock IS committed: CI must resolve the exact dependency graph rather
# than a fresh resolution that could pull a license-tainted or edition-
# incompatible transitive. The lock also backs the CI freshness gate.
# (Downstream library consumers still resolve their own graph — a committed lock
# does not constrain them.)

# The 4 MiB dfvfs UFS2 Tier-1 oracle image (tests/data/ufs2.raw) and its small
# extracted fixtures (ufs2_*.bin) ARE committed — they are well under the ~10 MiB
# crates.io tarball limit and are excluded from the published .crate anyway (see
# forensic/Cargo.toml `exclude`). Any larger, re-downloadable UFS1 corpus added
# later should be gitignored here.

# OS / editor cruft (belt-and-suspenders alongside a machine-wide core.excludesfile).
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
